Mask Detection With Limited Data

In this project I showcased how to train a model with very limited data (in this case 100 images)

The way it works is we use a method called "transfer learning", in which we freeze pretrain layers that are trained on similar data or cases and then only train the deeper layers.

In this case we'll be using yolo v8 model, which was already trained on COCO dataset which works well with faces and should adapt well to training on mask detection.

In[4]:
model = YOLO('yolov8s.pt')

Downloading https://github.com/ultralytics/assets/releases/download/v8.3.0/yolov8s.pt to 'yolov8s.pt': 100%  21.5MB 201.9MB/s 0.1s

In this case we will freeze the first 10 layers, which are responsible for a more abstract data extraction which we don't want to change, we want to change the more complex features (in this case masks).

In[5]:
model.freeze = [0, 10]

Augmentation is another core principle to implementing this model, since we have very limited data we'll set augment=true so the model will think there are many images instead of the only 100 we provided. It works by flipping, zooming in and changing colors of the images we provided and by doing that, it creates more data to learn from.

In[6]:
model.train(
    data='mask_dataset.yaml',
    epochs=50,
    imgsz=640,
    batch=8,
    freeze=10,
    name='mask_detector_small_data',
    augment=True,     # Enable strong augmentation
)
